---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---
<BaseLayout title="About — Behnaz" description="A bit about me, my path, and what I'm working on.">
  <section class="rise">
    <div class="page-head">
      <p class="eyebrow">about</p>
      <h1>A Little Intro</h1>
      <p class="lede">
        The long version — who I am, where I've been, and what I think about.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="prose">
      <p>
        I'm <strong>Behnaz</strong>, a data scientist and researcher with a
        background in <em>photonics, mechanical engineering, and a stubborn
        love of asking why</em>. I grew up in Mashhad, did my bachelor's in
        mechanical engineering, and then moved to Germany for a master's in
        Lasers and Photonics at Ruhr University Bochum.
      </p>
      <p>
        These days I work at the
        <a href="https://www.medit.hia.rwth-aachen.de/">Chair of Medical
        Information Technology (MedIT)</a> at RWTH Aachen, where I build
        deep-learning models that read body temperature from thermal infrared
        images — somewhere at the intersection of optics, machine learning,
        and bedside medicine.
      </p>
      <h2>What I think about</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Turning messy experimental data into something you can actually trust</li>
        <li>Where photonics meets machine learning — spectroscopy, thermal imaging, computational optics</li>
        <li>How to teach things clearly, especially the things I had to learn the hard way</li>
        <li>Good bread, good tea, and the slow rituals around them</li>
      </ul>
      <h2>Elsewhere</h2>
      <p>
        I read in three languages, write in two, and pretend to dream in
        German. Beyond the lab, I bake, sketch, take terrible film photos of
        nice clouds, and run on the Aachener Wald trails when the weather
        agrees.
      </p>
      <p>
        The best way to reach me is by
        <a href="mailto:hello@behnaz.example">email</a>. I usually reply
        within a day or two — unless there's a really good loaf of sourdough
        in the oven.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
